{"type":"text","timestamp":1773433374148,"sessionID":"ses_31723c412ffeI3LG1jZsgbAyRS","part":{"id":"prt_ce8ddad0d001syfNY2wzklrErX","sessionID":"ses_31723c412ffeI3LG1jZsgbAyRS","messageID":"msg_ce8dda3c7001JeOTebm48j2usf","type":"text","text":"Done. Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n**Problem:** When running `woco launch --all-ready` with no launchable tasks, the error message would generically suggest \"Use --all-ready to select all tasks...\" even though that flag was already passed. The hint text wasn't context-aware of which flags were active.\n\n**Fix:** Replaced the simple two-branch conditional with a three-way context-aware message system:\n\n1. **`--all-ready` only** (no other filters): Shows \"No launchable tasks found (all tasks are done, cancelled, or have unmet dependencies)\" — no misleading suggestion to use the already-active flag.\n\n2. **Specific filter flags** (with or without `--all-ready`): Shows which filters are active (e.g., `No tasks matched the current filters: --all-ready, --priority high`) and suggests broadening criteria.\n\n3. **No selection flags** (default behavior): Suggests using `--all-ready` or checking the task list — the only case where suggesting `--all-ready` makes sense.\n\nThe fix handles all selection flags: `--all-ready`, `--top-priority`, `--quickest-wins`, `--priority`, `--difficulty`, and `--tasks`.","time":{"start":1773433374144,"end":1773433374144}}}
